<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD (Reconditioning) -
        VALVES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="3">
        <title>VALVES</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Cleaning</title>
            <para>Remove all carbon from valve stems and valve heads using a suitable solvent and a fine brass wire
                brush.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspection</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Visually inspect each valve, replacing any that show evidence of burn marks, warpage,
                    scuffing or bending.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure each valve stem for wear using micrometer to measure valve stem diameter.
                    Measure at three locations 90&#176; apart. Refer to "
                    <hotlnk document="e435_HL4350301.xml" xrefid="hl4350301">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>. Replace valves if
                    out of specification.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure each valve stem and guide for fit of valve stem to guide clearance (running
                    clearance). Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e435_HL4350301.xml" xrefid="hl4350301">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>. Replace valve or
                    valve guide as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If valves are in serviceable condition, reface as required.</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Maintain a minimum valve face margin across the entire valve face,
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350333">3.33</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        . Refer to "
                        <hotlnk document="e435_HL4350301.xml" xrefid="hl4350301">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>. Use a caliper
                        to measure at four locations.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Maintain valve face angles as shown,
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350334">3.34</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>An insufficient margin will not provide proper heat dissipation and lead to warpage or
                                breakage.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Resurface valve face as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Refer to valve face dimensions in "
                        <hotlnk document="e435_HL4350301.xml" xrefid="hl4350301">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install valve in grinder and carefully dress the wheel to the proper angle.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove only the minimum amount of material necessary to true up the valve face.
                        Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350335">3.35</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Replace valve if margin is less than the specified minimum, after grinding.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Check valve face runout, after resurfacing, with a dial indicator. Replace valve if
                        beyond "
                        <hotlnk document="e435_HL4350301.xml" xrefid="hl4350301">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef4350333" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg11068" filename="../figcg1/CG11068.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 3.33 Measure Valve Face Margin</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4350334" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg5714" filename="../figcg5/CG5714.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 3.34 Valve Face Angles</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4350335" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg11069" filename="../figcg1/CG11069.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 3.35 Grinding Valve Face Angle</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
